article.description: — Douglas Wilson tied a season-high 23 points and Baylor Scheierman scored 22 and South Dakota State topped Oral Roberts 95-80 on Sunday.
article.headline: Wilson, Scheierman carry S. Dakota St. past Oral Roberts
article.linkText: Wilson, Scheierman carry S. Dakota St. past Oral Roberts
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- — Douglas Wilson tied a season-high 23 points and Baylor Scheierman scored 22 and South Dakota State topped Oral Roberts 95-80 on Sunday. Scheierman finished with a double-double collecting 11 rebounds whiled distributing seven assists. Alex Arians scored 15 with 10 rebounds for South Dakota State (12-5, 8-3 Summit League) and Charlie Easley scored 12. The 95 points were a season high for South Dakota State. Max Abmas scored 30 points for the Golden Eagles (11-9, 8-4) and Kareem Thompson scored 18. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
